the voice carry still across these dull great plain grow louder everyday sinking back to habit die hard your arm be so familiar these wound that time wo n't heal fester with hate so pick the scab and turn the page until the lion lears to write , the hunter will be glorify flip the switch and here I sit on the outside eight dollar haircut ( fuck you ) these word be my leash that I can untie drag meinto this night cover my ear , but still you call my name I will follow you ( deep into this night ) dim the light and tighten this noose I have lose myself in you I wo n't settle for anything less not one if us immune _____________________ name prelude to Pain Artist the kill tree album the Romance of Helen Trent